This schema allow to perform system operations on the Domogik application
like start or stop a module.

DOMOGIK.SYSTEM Message Specification

    * Class = DOMOGIK
    * Type = SYSTEM

This schema provides basic information relating to domogik internal processes

=== XPL-TRIG Structure ===
xpl.trig message should be sent as an acknowledgement to a xpl.cmnd command.

DOMOGIK.SYSTEM
{
COMMAND=command to send
MODULE=name of the module concerned by the command|*
HOST=Host sending the message
[FORCE=0|1]
[ERROR=error message if error occurs, 255 char max]
}

=== XPL-CMND Structure ===

DOMOGIK.SYSTEM
{
COMMAND=command to send
MODULE=name of the module concerned by the command|*
HOST=name of the host where a component should be started/stopped
[FORCE=0|1]
}

=== XPL-STAT Structure ===


HBEAT.*
{
(hbeat items)
}

Schema Specific Notes
COMMAND value can be one of :

* START : Start a component (managed by Domogik Manager)
* STOP : Stop a component (managed by the component)
* PING : Ask all components to reply (MODULE should equals '*', FORCE isn't used) (managed by each component)
* HOST-PING : Ask all hosts to reply (MODULE, FORCE aren't used) (managed by Domogik manager)
* RELOAD : If the component is able to do, refresh its config and reload it. (managed by the component)
* DUMP : If the component is able to do, dump its running config over Xpl. (managed by the component)
